-- Juventus Coach Conte’s Suspension Reduced After Appeal
-- B y   D a n   L i e f g r e e n
-- 2012-10-05T14:30:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-05/juventus-coach-conte-s-suspension-reduced-after-appeal.html
Juventus Coach Antonio Conte’s
suspension was reduced by an arbitration panel to Dec. 8,
according to a statement posted on the Italian National Olympics
Committee. In August Conte received a 10-month suspension for
failing to report a match-fixing case.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Liefgreen at 
 dliefgreen@bloomberg.net  